In Lean, `f =ᵐ[μL] g` is defined as `f =ᶠ[ae μL] g`, where `ae μL` is the filter of sets that are full measure with respect to `μL` (i.e., their complements have measure zero). Here, `=ᶠ[F]` means "equal eventually with respect to filter `F`", which in the case of `ae μL` translates to equality except on a set of measure zero. 

